==Old English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʃæaft/}}

===Etymology 1===
Germanic ''*skaftaz''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[sceft]], Old Saxon [[scaft]] (Dutch [[schaft]]), Old High German [[scaft]] (German [[Schaft]]), Old Norse [[skaft]] (Swedish [[skaft]]).

====Noun====
'''sceaft''' ''m'' (plural '''[[sceaftas]]''')
# [[shaft]], [[pole]]

===Etymology 2===
From [[scieppan]].

====Noun====
'''sceaft''' ''n/f'' (plural '''[[sceaftu]]''')
# [[creation]]; something created

